zzati, Dante, Alan Moore, Reinhard Kleist, Marcel Proust und Joann Sfar.  aUntil now, scholars in literary and cultural studies have barely touched upon the multiple points of engagement between comics and literature. Drawing on a number of specific examples, the contributors to this volume illustrate the diversity of issues that arise in looking at the relationship between comics and literature. The book includes a consideration of the works of Alberto Breccia, Dino Buzzati, Dante, Alan Moore, Reinhard Kleist, Marcel Proust, and Joann Sfar.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aArt and literature. 0aComic books, strips, etcxHistory and criticism. 0aComic books, strips, etc.xHistory and criticism. 0aLiteraturexAdaptationsxHistory and criticism. 4aComics. 4aIntermedialiät. 4aLiteraturadaption. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh  aComics.  aIntermediality.  aLiterature Adaptation.1 aBacke, Hans-Joachim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBanhold, Lars, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFigueira, Dorothy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrünewald, Dietrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHölter, Achim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHölter, Eva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHöppner, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLampart, Fabian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLohse, Rolf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPlatthaus, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmitz-Emans, Monika, econtributor.4ctb